HEADWORD: Tolane
<hw>To*lane"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Toluene</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A hydrocarbon,
<chform>C14H10</chform>, related both to the acetylene and the aromatic
series, and produced artificially as a white crystalline substance; --
called also <altname>diphenyl acetylene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
